  "body": "IP addresses of peers that are lost should maybe be forgotten faster than seems to be the case now.\n\nMost people working on private networks will first connect to the public network to learn. This makes their nodes' IP addresses known and remembered by nodes in the public network, which will in turn try to re-integrate 'lost nodes' forever (?) and cause constant traffic even when those nodes have moved on to form a private network, connecting to the now-private nodes, only to disconnect as soon as a new, private network id is detected.\n",
